We may never know the number of people killed in and around Tiananmen Square.
The  government said that 300 soldiers, "thugs", and bystanders were killed.
Other estimates  on Saturday and Sunday.
Estimates of death range all the way up to 12,000.To most that  figure seems too high, but the government figure is too low, and the government will not  provide further details.
Beijing University students say that 150 fellow students are missing.
There are rumors  that troops burned the bodies of demonstrators who were killed while huddling around  the "Goddess of Democracy" statue they had built. 
